  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That means a quantity of the people was-- I don't know how many, but we were only a part of the-- before the war, there were 35,000 Jews in Crakow.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "During the beginning-- after the beginning of the war or after the beginning of the occupation, with the beginning of the persecution of the Jews, let's say in '39, beginning of '40-- or during '40, they brought very many, many, many Jews from the villages around Crakow and the small places around Crakow.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So part of them, they were-- they were killed and then-- but the other part, the people who were so-called strong enough to work, were brought to Crakow.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we are getting more than we were before the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at the time, we were less and less and less and less.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember the-- how many we were, but I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Can you tell us what happened during the liquidation of the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] At least a month, I think, before the liquidation-- maybe two months-- they divided the ghetto into an A and B.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we felt that something has-- has to-- to become with us, and something has to occur, because all the people who were working were put in ghetto A, and all that elderly and not working and very, very young and sick and the hospital-- and so hospitalized people and so on were put in ghetto B.",
      "word_count": 58
    }
  ],
